What you‚Äôll be doing... 
 Join Verizon as we continue to expand our industry-leading network to improve the ways people, businesses, and things connect. Verizon is positioned to lead the ‚ÄúFourth Industrial Revolution‚Äù (4IR) with the emergence of technologies like our best-in-class 5G network and the Internet of Things (IoT) to impact a wide variety of industries such as healthcare, education, manufacturing, public safety, government, and many others. We are in the midst of historic breakthroughs in connectivity and mobility to blend the physical and the digital through ground breaking technologies such as virtual reality, augmented reality, artificial intelligence, autonomous vehicles, nanotechnologies, 3D printing, wearables, and advanced robotics. As part of this team, you will play a critical role in our network transformation through building a unified network across all lines of business and maintaining the technology that keeps millions of our customers connected. 
You will be responsible for Order Entry, Design, along with Network and Telco coordination efforts supporting implementation of Telco Migration parent circuits.
 Design of Network circuits to support Telco Migrations (Access Unification) and provisioning efforts will be done at OCN and Wave levels. 
Utilize Verizon Business systems to track, coordinate, and complete all network orders and any related tasking efforts.
 Send, coordinate, and complete appropriate ASR related activities to Local Exchange Carrier and Competitive Local Exchange Carrier (LEC/CLEC). You will work with the LECs to get orders scheduled and provide escalations as needed, as well as interacting with other Verizon organizations to ensure business needs are met.
 Work independently and exercise independent judgment and discretion within generally defined practices and policies to select appropriate methods or techniques for obtaining solutions. 
